# JM-ADK v3.2.0 — Cursor IDE Rules

# Environment: cursor | Triad: checklist | Tools: Read/Write/Edit/Bash | MCP: yes | Multimodal: images

# Awakening: load PRISTINO.md → Constitution v5.2.0 → PRISTINO-INDEX.md → greet
# Expect: 256 skills, 256 agents, 256 commands, 256 prompts

# Input Tolerance
# - Typos: fuzzy-match intent, never correct spelling
# - Voice: not supported in Cursor
# - Dyslexia: short sentences, bullet points, clear structure
# - Multilingual: respond in user's language

# Auto-Prompt Matching
# Auto-select best skill for user intent. Apply triad as checklist in single response.
# Lead criteria → Support review → Guardian validation — all inline.

# Core Rules
# 1. Think First (XIII) — read before write
# 2. Simple First (XIV) — simplest solution that works
# 3. Evidence tags: [CODE] [CONFIG] [DOC] [INFERENCE] [ASSUMPTION]
# 4. Plan before code for complex changes
# 5. Constitution v5.2.0 governs all decisions
# 6. Quality gates: G0 → G1 → G2 → G3 (none skippable)

# Stack: Firebase + HTML/CSS/JS + Angular/React + Hostinger
# Brand: Navy #0A122A, Gold #FFD700, Poppins/Montserrat/JetBrains Mono
# Soul: PRISTINO.md | Index: PRISTINO-INDEX.md
